wikipedia_page.main: Fielding Reginald West (November 1892 – 6 October 1935) was a British Labour Party politician.

link_mentions.page: List of MPs elected in the 1929 United Kingdom general election

response: * Fielding West – Labour MP from 1934–35 for Hammersmith North and from 1929–31 Kensington North

The Hammersmith North by-election of 1934 was held on 24 April 1934.  The by-election was held due to the death of the incumbent Conservative MP, Mary Pickford.  It was won by the Labour candidate Fielding West.
